answers.body_markdown:
The Form component uses request handlers ([symfony docs](https://symfony.com/doc/current/components/form.html#request-handling)) to handle requests in the `handleRequest()` method. From the linked documentation:

&gt; To process form data, you&#39;ll need to call the [`handleRequest()`](https://github.com/symfony/symfony/blob/4.3/src/Symfony/Component/Form/Form.php) method:
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; ```php
&gt; $form-&gt;handleRequest();
&gt; ```
&gt;
&gt; Behind the scenes, this uses a [`NativeRequestHandler`](https://github.com/symfony/symfony/blob/4.3/src/Symfony/Component/Form/NativeRequestHandler.php) object to read data off of the correct PHP superglobals (i.e. `$_POST` or `$_GET`) based on the HTTP method configured on the form (POST is default).

If you want to use the `Request` object from the HttpFoundation, you might want to configure the Form component to us the [`HttpFoundationRequestHandler`](https://github.com/symfony/form/blob/master/Extension/HttpFoundation/HttpFoundationRequestHandler.php) instead. In that case, you have to pass the `$request` argument to the `handleRequest()` method.

