&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;def vymazatVybrane(request):
    jedlo = VyberJedla.objects.all().&lt;b&gt;update(vybrane=False)&lt;/b&gt;
    return redirect(&#39;/&#39;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

If you want to only set a subset of the `VyberJedla` records, you need to [**`.filter(..)`** [Django-doc]](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/ref/models/querysets/#update) the queryset.

Note that usually GET methods are *not* supposed to change entities (and their values). You might consider making this a POST/PATCH request.

